intro: Elatinoides sieberi, commonly known as the slender elatin, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the family Elatinaceae and is characterized by its small, succulent leaves and delicate, yellowish flowers. The plant typically grows in sandy or rocky soils and is often found in coastal or inland regions. It is a short-lived annual or perennial species, often thriving in harsh, arid environments. Its botanical features make it an important component of the flora in its native habitats.
